  "On Friday night, routine hardware maintenance was started on the Project Sunrise Financial Data Warehouse.  The work was scheduled to complete on Sunday, but problems were encountered with a bad memory board on the database server.  The vendor was called and replacement hardware was delivered and installed on Sunday.  The restore is currently running and is scheduled to complete around 5": "30 pm today (Monday).  If the estimated completion time changes, we will update you.",

  "Pipeline integrity and safety have risen to new levels of public concern.  In the aftermath of the incidents at Bellingham, Washington and Carlsbad, New Mexico new pipeline safety regulations and legislation will require increased focus on pipeline integrity programs.  As a proactive approach to address these concerns, ETS Operations is establishing a Pipeline Integrity Program Management Group.  This group will be responsible for pipeline integrity issues for EOTT and ETS and financial reporting of EOTT's environmental and remediation projects.  The group will include the following functions": "corrosion, pipeline safety and pipeline integrity.",
  "Subject": "Organizational Announcement Email announcement_Final",

  "\u003c\u003c File": "EAMR Interconnect Services.doc \u003e\u003e",
  "Bcc": "g..stage@enron.com, david.marye@enron.com, don.hawkins@enron.com,",
  "Case A": "EAMR engineers, procures and constructs (EPC) the interconnect and/or measurement facilities for the customer.  The customer then holds title to the facilities and EAMR operates the facilities for them under a long term contract.  When the contract is terminated, the facilities are conveyed to either EAMR or the pipeline at a much smaller value (current market value for the used facilities at that point in the future).",
  "Case B": "EAMR does EPC, owns and operates the facilities and then contracts with the customer for a long term interconnect service fee (possibly in cents/MMBtu or a lump sum dollar amount monthly) to recover the capital with a good return and operating costs plus a margin.",

  "\u003c\u003c File": "EAMR Interconnect Services.doc \u003e\u003e",
  "Bcc": "g..stage@enron.com, david.marye@enron.com, don.hawkins@enron.com,",
  "Case A": "EAMR engineers, procures and constructs (EPC) the interconnect and/or measurement facilities for the customer.  The customer then holds title to the facilities and EAMR operates the facilities for them under a long term contract.  When the contract is terminated, the facilities are conveyed to either EAMR or the pipeline at a much smaller value (current market value for the used facilities at that point in the future).",
  "Case B": "EAMR does EPC, owns and operates the facilities and then contracts with the customer for a long term interconnect service fee (possibly in cents/MMBtu or a lump sum dollar amount monthly) to recover the capital with a good return and operating costs plus a margin.",
